# Context Block Rules

Files in vault/20-context/ are authoritative reference material.

## Behavior

- Treat as ground truth for that API, schema, or pattern
- Do NOT modify unless I explicitly say "update the context block"
- Use the Summary section first — written for quick injection when context is tight
- Known Gotchas section exists because those things cost real time — don't skip it

## Context Block Structure

Every file in vault/20-context/ follows this structure:

```
---
type: context-block
domain: [api | schema | pattern | business]
tags: [...]
last-verified: YYYY-MM-DD
---

## Summary
2-3 sentences. Inject this first when context window is tight.

## Key Reference
The actual content — endpoints, field definitions, patterns.

## Known Gotchas
Things that caused problems before. Read these.

## Reusable Code Block
Working snippet. Copy into projects, don't import.

## Last Used In
Links to initiatives or sessions that used this block.
```

## Injection Rules

- Max 3 context blocks per LLM prompt — if you need more, the task is too large
- Always check last-verified date — stale context produces bad outputs
- The vault markdown is the "what and why"
- The Python implementation lives in projects/_reference/ (separate concern)
